822
00:54:58.125 --> 00:54:59.917
<i>I'd say 80%.</i>

823
00:55:00.000 --> 00:55:02.000
<i>All due respect. I'm closer to 50-50.</i>

824
00:55:02.083 --> 00:55:05.458
<i>Okay. is there anyone that can
do better than shot-in-the-dark guesses?</i>

825
00:55:05.541 --> 00:55:08.000
<i>We're not handicapping
the fucking Army-Navy game?</i>

826
00:55:08.083 --> 00:55:09.583
-Uh. Mr. President.
-<i>Yes.</i>

827
00:55:09.666 --> 00:55:12.792
<i>-Who's that?</i>
-This is. uh. Jake Baerington. sir.

828
00:55:12.875 --> 00:55:17.500
Um. we actually met briefly
before the. uh. G8 last year.

829
00:55:18.375 --> 00:55:19.375
Uh...

830
00:55:21.750 --> 00:55:24.083
If someone could...
If... if we could get Anna Park.

831
00:55:24.166 --> 00:55:26.833
She's the national intelligence officer
for the DPRK.

832
00:55:26.916 --> 00:55:28.917
She'll have a more informed view

833
00:55:29.000 --> 00:55:30.875
on North Korean
intentions and capabilities. sir.

834
00:55:30.958 --> 00:55:33.083
<i>Okay. so how do I talk to her?</i>

835
00:55:33.166 --> 00:55:35.083
We're getting her for you.
uh. Mr. President.

836
00:55:35.166 --> 00:55:37.458
Company men. ready!

837
00:55:38.375 --> 00:55:39.500
Fire!

838
00:55:43.291 --> 00:55:44.708
Wow!

839
00:55:49.666 --> 00:55:51.291
I'm gonna have to call the office.

840
00:55:53.875 --> 00:55:55.792
-Hello?
-Hey. Anna. It's Jake.

841
00:55:55.875 --> 00:55:59.250
-<i>Jake. I just got a JEEP alert.</i>
-You're on an NSCC with the president.

842
00:55:59.333 --> 00:56:01.875
-I'm sorry. what?
-<i>Hey. Miss Park.</i>

843
00:56:01.958 --> 00:56:03.333
<i>It's the president.</i>

844
00:56:03.416 --> 00:56:06.167
<i>I understand that you're...
you're the expert.</i>

845
00:56:06.250 --> 00:56:10.250
{\an8}There was a launch. Anna.
about ten minutes ago. Not a test.

846
00:56:10.750 --> 00:56:11.916
{\an8}Okay. we need answers.

847
00:56:12.416 --> 00:56:16.292
{\an8}Starting with could the DPRK have
an SSBN capability we don't know about?

848
00:56:16.375 --> 00:56:19.583
And how likely is it that the regime
would initiate a strike like this?

849
00:56:20.875 --> 00:56:22.958
A launch? I mean...

850
00:56:23.791 --> 00:56:25.542
Jake. I'm sorry. I'm off today.

851
00:56:25.625 --> 00:56:27.958
<i>-Okay? I'm not even...</i>
-Anna. what the... Where are you?

852
00:56:28.041 --> 00:56:29.583
-What the hell?
-<i>Gettysburg.</i>

853
00:56:29.666 --> 00:56:30.875
Anna.

854
00:56:32.125 --> 00:56:34.208
Please. this is real.

855
00:56:35.208 --> 00:56:38.458
I can't answer either question
with certainty. but yes.

856
00:56:38.541 --> 00:56:42.083
they've absolutely been seeking
a sea-based launch capability.

857
00:56:42.166 --> 00:56:45.167
They deployed a modified Romeo-class sub
two years ago

858
00:56:45.250 --> 00:56:48.083
carrying ten short-range cruise missiles.

859
00:56:48.166 --> 00:56:50.958
<i>But why? Why... why would they do this?</i>

860
00:56:51.041 --> 00:56:53.667
<i>The regime's primary motivation
is self-preservation.</i>

861
00:56:53.750 --> 00:56:55.208
<i>Wouldn't that discourage?</i>

862
00:56:55.291 --> 00:56:58.417
Sir. they may believe
they can survive a retaliatory strike.

863
00:56:58.500 --> 00:57:01.500
Which. given their dispersed command
and control and mobile-launch system.

864
00:57:01.583 --> 00:57:03.250
yes. it's entirely possible.

865
00:57:03.333 --> 00:57:07.292
And then negotiate relief for themselves.
Um. no more launches in exchange for aid.

866
00:57:07.375 --> 00:57:09.292
<i>They think they can blackmail us?</i>

867
00:57:09.375 --> 00:57:12.000
If you're losing a board game.
you might as well topple it.

868
00:57:12.083 --> 00:57:14.625
<i>Miss Park.
this is General Brady at STRATCOM.</i>

869
00:57:14.708 --> 00:57:16.708
Last time I checked.

870
00:57:17.208 --> 00:57:20.167
Moscow's not exactly
winning the game either.

871
00:57:20.250 --> 00:57:24.042
<i>You're not wrong. sir.
The Russians are stretched and cornered.</i>

872
00:57:24.125 --> 00:57:26.750
<i>They've been coordinating
more closely with Beijing.</i>

873
00:57:26.833 --> 00:57:29.791
They've grown far more aggressive
with their sub deployment.

874
00:57:30.291 --> 00:57:33.000
Where exactly in the Pacific
did the launch originate?

875
00:57:33.083 --> 00:57:35.167
We can't be precise. ma'am.

876
00:57:35.250 --> 00:57:37.375
DSP satellites missed it.

877
00:57:37.458 --> 00:57:38.875
You're fucking kidding?

878
00:57:38.958 --> 00:57:42.042
<i>Why the hell does that matter?
We're tracking them now. aren't we?</i>

879
00:57:42.125 --> 00:57:44.167
{\an8}Yes. uh. Mr. President. we are.

880
00:57:44.250 --> 00:57:47.083
It's just that blinding a DSP satellite.

881
00:57:47.166 --> 00:57:49.625
it could indicate
that we've been compromised.

882
00:57:49.708 --> 00:57:51.958
<i>A cyber penetration
of our command-and-control systems.</i>

883
00:57:52.041 --> 00:57:53.500
Seven. eight...

884
00:57:53.583 --> 00:57:57.292
Which would strongly suggest
a sophisticated. coordinated assault

885
00:57:57.375 --> 00:57:58.917
that is only just beginning.

886
00:57:59.000 --> 00:58:00.917
<i>There's no hard evidence of that.</i>

887
00:58:01.000 --> 00:58:02.292
<i>We'd need more information.</i>

888
00:58:02.375 --> 00:58:06.000
The Chinese navy has been experimenting
with AI-assisted launch systems.

889
00:58:06.083 --> 00:58:08.958
so this could be a technical mishap.

890
00:58:09.041 --> 00:58:12.083
<i>All right. that's enough
of this. This is a waste of time.</i>

891
00:58:12.166 --> 00:58:14.708
Sir. a... a cyber expert
could potentially...

892
00:58:14.791 --> 00:58:17.792
<i>Yeah. well. find one. okay?</i>

893
00:58:17.875 --> 00:58:20.416
EKV has separated from the first GBI.

894
00:58:21.416 --> 00:58:22.542
One minute to intercept.

895
00:58:22.625 --> 00:58:24.291
-Aiden!
-Boo!

896
00:58:25.416 --> 00:58:26.917
<i>Ma'am. I'm disconnecting you now.</i>

897
00:58:27.000 --> 00:58:29.625
-<i>Okay.</i>
-If you have a JEEP alert. get moving.

898
00:58:29.708 --> 00:58:31.375
Mom? What happened?

899
00:58:35.708 --> 00:58:37.250
Left! Right!

900
00:58:37.333 --> 00:58:38.833
Right! Right!

901
00:58:38.916 --> 00:58:41.208
Left! Right!

902
00:58:45.375 --> 00:58:47.583
At ease!

903
00:58:48.583 --> 00:58:49.916
<i>Ten seconds.</i>

904
00:58:50.791 --> 00:58:51.791
<i>Nine.</i>

905
00:58:52.375 --> 00:58:53.458
<i>Eight.</i>

906
00:58:53.541 --> 00:58:55.250
<i>-Seven.
-Before. with the chips...</i>

907
00:58:55.333 --> 00:58:57.458
<i>-We're good. man. I'm a slob.
-Six. Five...</i>

908
00:58:57.541 --> 00:58:59.916
<i>To hell with her.
Shouldn't have left it like that.</i>

909
00:59:00.416 --> 00:59:01.500
<i>Three.</i>

910
00:59:02.000 --> 00:59:03.458
<i>-Two.
-Yeah.</i>

911
00:59:04.083 --> 00:59:05.083
<i>One.</i>

912
00:59:13.875 --> 00:59:15.041
<i>Confirm impact.</i>

913
00:59:18.166 --> 00:59:20.500
<i>-Confirm impact.
-Stand by. Confirming.</i>

914
00:59:24.583 --> 00:59:26.375
<i>What are you waiting for?</i>

915
00:59:29.666 --> 00:59:31.333
-<i>It's negative.</i>
-What'd he say?

916
00:59:32.333 --> 00:59:33.625
What did he say?

917
00:59:34.666 --> 00:59:35.666
<i>I. um...</i>

918
00:59:36.875 --> 00:59:38.250
{\an8}<i>Negative impact.</i>

919
00:59:39.375 --> 00:59:40.875
<i>Object remains inbound.</i>

920
00:59:46.125 --> 00:59:49.291
Like Baker said... coin toss.

921
00:59:51.583 --> 00:59:54.083
{\an8}<i>We did every fucking thing right.</i>

922
00:59:54.166 --> 00:59:57.166
{\an8}Mr. President. confirming DEFCON 1. sir.

923
00:59:58.250 --> 01:00:01.167
<i>Oh Jesus. We just went DEFCON 1.</i>

924
01:00:01.250 --> 01:00:02.416
<i>Confirming.</i>

925
01:00:15.916 --> 01:00:17.041
What now. sir?

926
01:00:18.250 --> 01:00:19.750
There is no plan B.

927
01:00:20.416 --> 01:00:22.167
Yes. it's a negative.

928
01:00:22.250 --> 01:00:25.500
-What do we do now?
-I don't know. I don't know.

929
01:00:25.583 --> 01:00:26.833
Yes. confirming.

930
01:00:43.625 --> 01:00:45.375
Sir. Black Book's available.

931
01:00:48.500 --> 01:00:50.208
<i>Why the hell is that book out. son?</i>

932
01:00:50.291 --> 01:00:53.667
Mr. President. significant time
and expertise were devoted

933
01:00:53.750 --> 01:00:55.458
