952
01:01:51.333 --> 01:01:53.708
<i>Mr. President. Mr. Baerington.</i>

953
01:01:53.791 --> 01:01:57.000
<i>slowing down is one luxury
we just don't have.</i>

954
01:01:57.708 --> 01:01:59.542
These are the circumstances.

955
01:01:59.625 --> 01:02:03.750
In little more than seven minutes.
we will lose the city of Chicago.

956
01:02:03.833 --> 01:02:05.750
I can't tell you why.

957
01:02:06.458 --> 01:02:09.750
Or why we're seeing
North Korea. Russia. China.

958
01:02:09.833 --> 01:02:13.375
Pakistan. and even Iran
raising their alerts

959
01:02:13.458 --> 01:02:16.875
and mobilizing their forces
across air. land. and sea.

960
01:02:18.083 --> 01:02:20.833
Perhaps. as Mr. Baerington
suggested earlier.

961
01:02:20.916 --> 01:02:24.750
<i>they are simply and innocently
responding to our posture.</i>

962
01:02:24.833 --> 01:02:26.333
<i>It is also possible</i>

963
01:02:26.416 --> 01:02:30.750
<i>that they've seen our homeland
is about to absorb a catastrophic blow.</i>

964
01:02:30.833 --> 01:02:33.417
<i>and they are readying
to take advantage of that.</i>

965
01:02:33.500 --> 01:02:37.250
Or this is all part of
a phased. coordinated assault.

966
01:02:37.333 --> 01:02:38.750
with far worse to come.

967
01:02:38.833 --> 01:02:40.333
I simply don't know.

968
01:02:40.416 --> 01:02:42.708
What I do know is this.

969
01:02:42.791 --> 01:02:48.292
If we do not take steps
to neutralize our enemies now.

970
01:02:48.375 --> 01:02:51.042
we will lose our window to do so.

971
01:02:51.125 --> 01:02:53.292
<i>We can strike preemptively.</i>

972
01:02:53.375 --> 01:02:57.250
<i>or risk 100 ICBMs launching our way.</i>

973
01:02:57.333 --> 01:03:01.083
at which time.
this war will have already been lost.

974
01:03:05.875 --> 01:03:07.375
{\an8}<i>And if there is no war?</i>

975
01:03:10.000 --> 01:03:10.750
<i>If this is it?</i>

976
01:03:10.833 --> 01:03:13.875
I think we'd all welcome
any indication of that.

977
01:03:13.958 --> 01:03:17.292
{\an8}As unfathomable as it was
just five minutes ago.

978
01:03:17.375 --> 01:03:19.583
{\an8}I'd accept the loss
of ten million Americans

979
01:03:19.666 --> 01:03:22.750
{\an8}if I could be absolutely certain
it stops there.

980
01:03:22.833 --> 01:03:27.167
Of course. in absence of that certainty.
we can all certainly say a prayer

981
01:03:27.250 --> 01:03:31.667
{\an8}and rely on the goodwill
of our adversaries to keep us safe.

982
01:03:31.750 --> 01:03:36.333
{\an8}Or we can hit their command centers.
silos. and bombers

983
01:03:36.416 --> 01:03:38.208
while they're still on the ground.

984
01:03:38.291 --> 01:03:42.333
eliminating their ability
to take further action against us.

985
01:03:44.666 --> 01:03:47.833
We've already lost
one American city today.

986
01:03:49.333 --> 01:03:50.542
How many more do you wanna risk?

987
01:03:50.625 --> 01:03:52.333
<i>What kind of question is that?</i>

988
01:03:53.625 --> 01:03:56.416
<i>-This is insanity. okay?</i>
-No. sir.

989
01:03:58.458 --> 01:03:59.958
This is reality.

990
01:04:00.541 --> 01:04:01.750
Six minutes to impact.

991
01:04:01.833 --> 01:04:05.125
It's Walker. She's got
the Russian foreign minister on the line.

992
01:04:05.208 --> 01:04:06.791
We can't merge the calls.

993
01:04:09.250 --> 01:04:10.250
Jake.

994
01:04:10.916 --> 01:04:12.875
Sit room has
the Russian foreign minister on the line.

995
01:04:12.958 --> 01:04:15.000
but we cannot merge the call.

996
01:04:15.750 --> 01:04:18.500
You need to pick up and take it.

997
01:04:19.791 --> 01:04:21.625
It has to be you.

998
01:04:23.208 --> 01:04:24.208
Okay?

999
01:04:24.833 --> 01:04:28.333
The president needs a reason
not to retaliate. okay? You give him one.

1000
01:04:31.083 --> 01:04:32.416
-You ready?
-Yeah.

1001
01:04:33.083 --> 01:04:34.250
Let's go.

1002
01:04:35.541 --> 01:04:37.375
This is Jake Baerington.

1003
01:04:37.458 --> 01:04:41.125
-I'm the deputy national security advisor.
-<i>You authorized to speak?</i>

1004
01:04:41.208 --> 01:04:44.500
I'm authorized to do whatever's necessary
to de-escalate this situation. sir.

1005
01:04:44.583 --> 01:04:48.792
<i>Your bombers are airborne.
What kind of de-escalation is that?</i>

1006
01:04:48.875 --> 01:04:50.208
Mr. Foreign Minister.

1007
01:04:50.291 --> 01:04:52.708
you have to understand
that's only a precaution.

1008
01:04:53.583 --> 01:04:55.375
Okay. our country is about to be hit

1009
01:04:55.458 --> 01:04:58.625
by an entirely unprecedented
and unprovoked attack.

1010
01:04:58.708 --> 01:05:00.792
<i>Which we had nothing to do with.</i>

1011
01:05:00.875 --> 01:05:02.250
Do I have your word?

1012
01:05:02.333 --> 01:05:05.250
Can I assure the president
that Russia has nothing to do with this.

1013
01:05:05.333 --> 01:05:08.542
<i>they're not behind the launch.
and you will not seek to capitalize?</i>

1014
01:05:08.625 --> 01:05:09.708
Yes.

1015
01:05:10.541 --> 01:05:11.875
And do I have your word

1016
01:05:12.541 --> 01:05:15.792
that you won't use it as an excuse
to wipe us out?

1017
01:05:15.875 --> 01:05:18.083
-That's ridiculous.
-<i>Is it?</i>

1018
01:05:18.166 --> 01:05:19.625
<i>You might tell your president.</i>

1019
01:05:19.708 --> 01:05:24.458
<i>if your forces do not stand down.
we will be compelled to respond in kind.</i>

1020
01:05:25.250 --> 01:05:28.000
You have a sub off our coast
that just slipped its shadow.

1021
01:05:28.083 --> 01:05:31.125
<i>Order it to the surface
to identify its location</i>

1022
01:05:31.208 --> 01:05:32.542
<i>as a show of good faith.</i>

1023
01:05:32.625 --> 01:05:34.708
So you can wipe it out of the water?

1024
01:05:34.791 --> 01:05:37.250
We are running out of time.

1025
01:05:37.333 --> 01:05:39.083
and my wife is six months...

1026
01:05:41.666 --> 01:05:42.583
<i>Jake.</i>

1027
01:05:42.666 --> 01:05:44.458
I'm sorry. Um...

1028
01:05:46.500 --> 01:05:47.667
Jake?

1029
01:05:47.750 --> 01:05:49.625
<i>Listen. if we get this wrong.</i>

1030
01:05:50.458 --> 01:05:52.375
none of us are gonna be alive tomorrow.

1031
01:05:52.458 --> 01:05:55.042
Now. if you're telling me
that you didn't do this.

1032
01:05:55.125 --> 01:05:56.458
<i>and I believe you.</i>

1033
01:05:56.541 --> 01:05:59.458
<i>then I can promise you
we will not hit any Russian targets.</i>

1034
01:05:59.541 --> 01:06:03.875
<i>Can you promise me you will stand down
your long-range strategic assets?</i>

1035
01:06:03.958 --> 01:06:06.875
<i>Better. There'll be no retaliation at all.</i>

1036
01:06:06.958 --> 01:06:08.042
I completely agree.

1037
01:06:08.125 --> 01:06:11.125
<i>And I will push for that.
but that is not my decision. sir.</i>

1038
01:06:11.208 --> 01:06:13.125
If you do retaliate.

1039
01:06:13.208 --> 01:06:18.000
can you guarantee that your response
will not infringe on our airspace?

1040
01:06:22.583 --> 01:06:24.917
With our bombers. yes. of course.

1041
01:06:25.000 --> 01:06:26.250
And missiles?

1042
01:06:26.333 --> 01:06:29.833
If you determine that. God.
fucking China is responsible...

1043
01:06:29.916 --> 01:06:32.083
-Sir. there...
-Tell the truth.

1044
01:06:32.791 --> 01:06:33.791
No.

1045
01:06:37.125 --> 01:06:39.583
Sir. we both know
that there would be some overflight.

1046
01:06:39.666 --> 01:06:41.083
<i>There's no way around that.</i>

1047
01:06:41.166 --> 01:06:43.833
And you expect us to simply trust

1048
01:06:43.916 --> 01:06:47.167
that warheads flying over our head
are not destined on our cities?

1049
01:06:47.250 --> 01:06:50.041
<i>Hopefully. sir.
there will not be any warheads.</i>

1050
01:06:51.000 --> 01:06:55.541
If there are. then. yes.
I'm asking you to trust me.

1051
01:06:59.458 --> 01:07:00.666
Trust.

1052
01:07:01.708 --> 01:07:02.708
Why?

1053
01:07:04.083 --> 01:07:06.250
<i>-I'll talk to my president.</i>
-What if. um...

1054
01:07:14.208 --> 01:07:15.792
<i>Darkstar. this is Ghost 1.</i>

1055
01:07:15.875 --> 01:07:17.625
Approaching loiter position.

1056
01:07:19.500 --> 01:07:21.667
<i>Ghost 1-1. Darkstar. Picture clean.</i>

1057
01:07:21.750 --> 01:07:23.458
<i>Stand by mission data package.</i>

1058
01:07:31.083 --> 01:07:32.666
Is this right?

1059
01:07:33.625 --> 01:07:35.833
Darkstar. Ghost. MDB confirmed.

1060
01:07:37.791 --> 01:07:40.333
<i>Ghost. Darkstar. Stand by execution order.</i>

1061
01:07:42.708 --> 01:07:45.167
Forward-deployed B-2s
are at loitering position.

1062
01:07:45.250 --> 01:07:47.833
Mr. President.
we're going to need your decision.

1063
01:07:48.333 --> 01:07:51.750
Lieutenant Commander Reeves
is your strike advisor

1064
01:07:52.250 --> 01:07:55.417
and can walk you through
the authentication process.

1065
01:07:55.500 --> 01:07:58.917
Then you'll need to read aloud
an attack option designation...

1066
01:07:59.000 --> 01:08:01.417
<i>Yeah. Look.
I understand all that. all right?</i>

1067
01:08:01.500 --> 01:08:03.708
<i>Reid. I need you.</i>

1068
01:08:05.583 --> 01:08:06.750
<i>What do you think. Reid?</i>

1069
01:08:06.833 --> 01:08:08.625
<i>We're close to take off.</i>

1070
01:08:08.708 --> 01:08:10.000
<i>Did we lose him?</i>

1071
01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:12.541
{\an8}<i>Sir! No. no. no. no. sir!</i>

1072
01:08:13.041 --> 01:08:14.833
{\an8}<i>Holy shit!</i>

1073
01:08:15.416 --> 01:08:16.833
-<i>What was that?</i>
-All right.

1074
01:08:16.916 --> 01:08:18.458
<i>Mr. President?</i>

1075
01:08:18.541 --> 01:08:21.292
<i>-It's Jake again. sir. Baerington.</i>
-Keep your seats. Keep your seats.

1076
01:08:21.375 --> 01:08:23.417
{\an8}<i>I spoke to the Russian foreign minister.</i>

1077
01:08:23.500 --> 01:08:26.958
He denies their responsibility
for the launch.

1078
01:08:27.625 --> 01:08:30.750
Said he spoke to Beijing.
and he doesn't think it was them either.

1079
01:08:33.416 --> 01:08:35.916
-I believed him. sir.
-<i>You did?</i>

1080
01:08:36.500 --> 01:08:39.666
<i>-They gonna back down?</i>
-Sir. I think that they want to.

1081
01:08:40.750 --> 01:08:43.333
And if we can guarantee
that we will not retaliate.

1082
01:08:43.416 --> 01:08:44.875
I think I can. uh...

1083
01:08:46.416 --> 01:08:48.333
we can convince them.

1084
01:08:48.416 --> 01:08:51.041
<i>-What does that mean?
-We don't launch.</i>

1085
01:08:51.958 --> 01:08:53.250
<i>Against anyone.</i>

1086
01:08:53.916 --> 01:08:54.917
<i>For now. at least.</i>

1087
01:08:55.000 --> 01:08:57.833
<i>What. we just sit back
and watch Chicago incinerate?</i>

1088
01:08:58.375 --> 01:09:01.583
{\an8}<i>Are you fucking kidding me? Do you think
the American people are gonna go for that?</i>

1089
01:09:01.666 --> 01:09:04.542
<i>Sir. the... the warhead.
it might still malfunction.</i>

1090
01:09:04.625 --> 01:09:06.250
<i>They do that sometimes.</i>

1091
01:09:06.333 --> 01:09:08.666
<i>Did he agree to these terms?</i>

1092
01:09:09.166 --> 01:09:12.208
<i>All right. we do nothing.
they back off for certain?</i>

1093
01:09:12.291 --> 01:09:14.292
-More or less.
-<i>More or less?!</i>

1094
01:09:14.375 --> 01:09:15.792
<i>-Jake.
-Yes. sir.</i>

1095
01:09:15.875 --> 01:09:17.750
<i>I'm gonna need you to breathe.</i>

1096
01:09:17.833 --> 01:09:18.958
I'm breathing just fine. sir.

1097
01:09:19.041 --> 01:09:22.583
<i>Good 'cause my job is
to make this decision. I wish it weren't.</i>

1098
01:09:22.666 --> 01:09:26.375
<i>And your job is to tell me
exactly what he agreed to.</i>

1099
01:09:27.250 --> 01:09:30.083
<i>-No bullshit. Can you do that?</i>
-He didn't agree to anything. sir.

1100
01:09:30.166 --> 01:09:32.083
He said
he needed to speak with his president.

1101
01:09:32.583 --> 01:09:34.958
Sounds to me like we know nothing new.

1102
01:09:35.041 --> 01:09:37.750
<i>Wrong. General. If we do what he's asking.</i>

1103
01:09:37.833 --> 01:09:39.917
<i>if we hold back.
there's at least a chance.</i>

1104
01:09:40.000 --> 01:09:41.458
Two minutes and 30 seconds.

1105
01:09:41.541 --> 01:09:44.583
<i>Jake. Jake. I do what you're suggesting.</i>

1106
01:09:45.791 --> 01:09:48.041
<i>I let whoever did this get away with it.</i>

1107
01:09:48.541 --> 01:09:50.417
<i>How is that any different
from surrendering?</i>

1108
01:09:50.500 --> 01:09:52.541
<i>Sir. if you wanna look at it that way.</i>

1109
01:09:53.166 --> 01:09:55.417
then I'm telling you your choices are

1110
01:09:55.500 --> 01:09:57.083
surrender or suicide.

1111
01:10:01.875 --> 01:10:03.000
Uh...

1112
01:10:08.333 --> 01:10:09.666
<i>We gonna need a minute.</i>

1113
01:10:11.833 --> 01:10:13.333
So what now? What are we doing?

1114
01:10:14.416 --> 01:10:15.958
Now I call Fort Belvoir.

1115
01:10:16.041 --> 01:10:18.666
Put the Army Corps of Engineers
on standby.

1116
01:10:19.666 --> 01:10:22.500
In case the White House gets hit
and they need to dig us out.

1117
01:10:22.583 --> 01:10:23.542
Oh God.

1118
01:10:23.625 --> 01:10:25.666
-Serious?
-That's the plan.

1119
01:10:27.583 --> 01:10:29.000
There's a plan for this?

1120
01:10:38.916 --> 01:10:40.375
If this order comes through...

1121
01:10:42.875 --> 01:10:44.375
I know my job. sir.

1122
01:11:00.166 --> 01:11:05.208
<i>Romeo. Bravo. Juliett. Whiskey.
Delta. Foxtrot. Echo.</i>

1123
01:11:05.291 --> 01:11:07.333
Missilization order is authentic.

1124
01:11:08.916 --> 01:11:10.417
Romeo. Bravo. Juliett.

1125
01:11:10.500 --> 01:11:13.042
Whiskey. Delta. Foxtrot. Echo.

1126
01:11:13.125 --> 01:11:14.583
I concur with missilization.

1127
01:11:15.666 --> 01:11:16.708
Three. two. one. Turn.

1128
01:11:16.791 --> 01:11:18.750
Sir. standing by for fire order.

1129
01:11:20.041 --> 01:11:22.083
Sir. your nuclear forces are ready.

1130
01:11:22.583 --> 01:11:24.708
-Sir. B-2s are at loiter.
-Yes. sir.

1131
01:11:24.791 --> 01:11:27.000
{\an8}Missile field status green.

1132
01:11:27.083 --> 01:11:28.916
{\an8}What if he doesn't come back on?

1133
01:11:30.541 --> 01:11:33.958
Decapitation event.
We find the vice president.

1134
01:11:34.041 --> 01:11:37.875
If we can't reach him. speaker.
Right on down the list.

1135
01:11:37.958 --> 01:11:39.166
<i>I'm here.</i>

1136
01:11:40.083 --> 01:11:42.916
<i>-You'll need your SAS card. sir.
-Oh.</i>

1137
01:11:45.708 --> 01:11:47.208
<i>It's in here somewhere.</i>

1138
01:11:48.041 --> 01:11:49.125
<i>Right.</i>

1139
01:11:50.041 --> 01:11:51.916
<i>Reminds me of when I was in college.</i>

1140
01:11:54.958 --> 01:11:57.208
<i>You just. uh. read it aloud.</i>

1141
01:11:59.708 --> 01:12:02.500
{\an8}<i>November. Delta. Oscar.</i>

1142
01:12:03.000 --> 01:12:05.917
{\an8}<i>One. one. one. seven.</i>

1143
01:12:06.000 --> 01:12:08.417
November. Delta. Oscar.

1144
01:12:08.500 --> 01:12:11.541
<i>One. one. one. seven.</i>

1145
01:12:13.333 --> 01:12:15.833
<i>National command authority confirmed.</i>

1146
01:12:17.625 --> 01:12:19.458
Your orders. Mr. President?

1147
01:12:20.208 --> 01:12:21.375
<i>My orders?</i>

1148
01:13:01.416 --> 01:13:03.708
You sure you don't want any coffee? Water?

1149
01:13:04.208 --> 01:13:05.625
No. thank you. ma'am.

1150
01:13:21.875 --> 01:13:24.083
Betty. can you get us the majority leader?

1151
01:13:24.166 --> 01:13:26.750
Quickly. please. Thanks.

1152
01:13:28.708 --> 01:13:30.500
Already 45 minutes late.

1153
01:13:33.583 --> 01:13:35.416
POTUS for majority leader. please.

1154
01:13:36.500 --> 01:13:37.500
Thank you.

1155
01:14:02.916 --> 01:14:04.625
That's looking more like it.

1156
01:14:22.125 --> 01:14:23.208
Nope.

1157
01:14:23.791 --> 01:14:25.125
Out playing nine.

1158
01:14:26.583 --> 01:14:28.041
It's going. I guess.

1159
01:14:28.541 --> 01:14:31.958
Last time I was around all these uniforms.
I was a private.

1160
01:14:32.583 --> 01:14:34.500
They're still full of shit.

1161
01:14:40.458 --> 01:14:42.500
Thanks. George. I appreciate that.

1162
01:14:43.625 --> 01:14:46.375
We were lucky to have 33 great years.

1163
01:14:47.083 --> 01:14:49.875
Meant the world you and Sheila
came to the funeral.

1164
01:14:52.083 --> 01:14:54.458
Okay. talk later.

1165
01:14:58.875 --> 01:14:59.875
Sir.

1166
01:15:01.000 --> 01:15:02.000
Sir.

1167
01:15:02.833 --> 01:15:04.208
-Thank you.
-Yeah.

1168
01:15:07.083 --> 01:15:08.583
Let's knock this in now.

1169
01:15:14.625 --> 01:15:16.833
<i>Hey. I was hoping to catch you.</i>

1170
01:15:17.541 --> 01:15:20.542
-I wish you were here to see this.
-<i>Yeah? Is it going good?</i>

1171
01:15:20.625 --> 01:15:23.625
<i>They say anything
that raises awareness helps.</i>

1172
01:15:23.708 --> 01:15:26.291
-Okay.
-<i>You sound tired.</i>

1173
01:15:26.791 --> 01:15:28.583
No. Um...

1174
01:15:29.208 --> 01:15:30.208
I'm fine.

1175
01:15:31.250 --> 01:15:35.000
My husband. the only politician
who can't lie to save his life.

1176
01:15:35.083 --> 01:15:36.875
Okay. I'm fucked.

1177
01:15:36.958 --> 01:15:39.208
You know. didn't they. uh.

1178
01:15:40.166 --> 01:15:41.791
promise that. uh.

1179
01:15:42.291 --> 01:15:44.042
we'd get used to it after a while?

1180
01:15:44.125 --> 01:15:47.000
<i>"Worse than the campaign."
I think that's what I remember.</i>

1181
01:15:47.083 --> 01:15:49.583
<i>I think they said
it would break us. actually.</i>

1182
01:15:49.666 --> 01:15:52.750
Oh. speaking of.
we have to talk about my mother.

1183
01:15:53.666 --> 01:15:56.333
Now the doctor's saying
she needs full-time help.

1184
01:15:59.291 --> 01:16:01.458
Hello? Are you there?

1185
01:16:01.958 --> 01:16:03.875
It's not just me. It's the doctor.

1186
01:16:03.958 --> 01:16:07.792
